Package: mixedlogitr
Type: Package
Title: R Parity Layer for the Mixed Logit Choice Lab
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Peterson", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "noreply@example.com")
Description: Companion R implementation that reads the Python project's
    canonical synthetic dataset, fits MNL and MXL with mlogit, and produces
    the same elasticity and WTP outputs. The point is cross-language
    reproducibility: estimates from this package should match the Python
    estimates to within numerical and SML simulation tolerance.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    mlogit (>= 1.1),
    dfidx,
    jsonlite,
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
